# Weather Report
A high-pressure system continues to dominate the Pacific Northwest, bringing warm and dry conditions to the Seattle area through the end of the week. Temperatures will rise into the low-mid 80s by Friday **5-7°F above normal for late February**.
 
Smoke transport from wildfires in eastern Washington and British Columbia may periodically affect visibility. Morning marine clouds near the coast will likely clear by late morning.
 
A weak system approaching this weekend could increase cloud cover and bring slight shower chances on Monday.
 
